											<header>
												<h2>Tools and Technologies</h2>
												<p>Things and Services we use to construct the Website</p>
											</header>

											<span class="image featured"><img src="images/tools.jpg" alt="" /></span>
											
											<h4>Tools:</h4>
											<p>	
												<b>1.	GitHub/Visual Studio,</b>
													We will be using GitHub or Visual Studio as these applications are compatible for team projects and what we are most familiar with.
													Moreover, these apps provide free local hosting service for working and updating the web while in the developing process. 
													<br>
												<b>2.	Text Editor (Notepad ++, Atom.io, etc) </b>
													This tool is very essential in the making of this project because editor is like the control panel of our website. 
													The code, page layout and functions are everything set in the text editor. In other words, without this tool we canâ€™t edit the appearance and how our website works.
													<br>	
												<b>3.	Open Source Template</b>
													We are planning to use template for our website instead of creating it from scratch.
													However, it is way easier to use templates because we already got the design and it is only matter of changing the text inside it. 
													<b>(html5up.com/templated.co)</b>
													<br>
												<b>4.	Bootstrap </b>
													Bootstrap is to provide functions in our website. 
													In order to make our website more interactive and arranged this tool is very essential. 
													By collaborating it with the text editor, we will get maximum function of this tool called Bootstrap.
													<b>(bootstrap4.com)</b>
											</p>

											<h4>Technologies:</h4>
											<p>
												<b>1.	Website Hosting Service</b>
													After all is done and we are sure that the website is adequately developed, the next step is to think about using a Web Hosting Service. 
													A service that allows us to release the website we made to public so that everybody all around the world can see and surf in our web. 
													There are 3 leading hosting companies which are Blue Host, HostGator and, Hostinger.com. 
													<br>
												<b>2.	Clouds (GitHub)</b>
													The Cloud technology held a huge role in this web making since we are using GitHub for our project. 
													Pushing and Pulling works to the GitHub repository in GitHub app is one example of the Cloud technology.
											</p>

